theorem
Th55: (M1 is  anti-circular implies ( - M1 ) is  anti-circular)
proof
A1: ( Indices M1 ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
assume M1 is  anti-circular;
then consider p being (FinSequence of K) such that A2: ( len p ) = ( width M1 ) and A3: M1 is_anti-circular_about p by CKB69:def 1;
set r = ( - p );
p is (Element of ( ( len p ) -tuples_on (the carrier of K) )) by FINSEQ_2:92;
then A4: ( - p ) is (Element of ( ( len p ) -tuples_on (the carrier of K) )) by FINSEQ_2:113;
A5: ( Indices ( - M1 ) ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
A6: ( width M1 ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
A7: (for i,j being Nat holds (([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( - M1 ) ) & i <= j) implies ( ( - M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( r . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len r ) ) + 1 ) )))
proof
let i being Nat,j being Nat;
assume that
A8: [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( - M1 ) )
and
A9: i <= j;
( ( ( j - i ) mod n ) + 1 ) in ( Seg n ) by A5,A8,CKB3:1;
then A10: ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) in ( dom p ) by A2,A6,FINSEQ_1:def 3;
( ( - M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( - ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by A1,A5,A8,MATRIX_3:def 2
.= ( ( comp K ) . ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by VECTSP_1:def 13
.= ( ( comp K ) . ( p . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by A3,A1,A5,A8,A9,CKB68:def 1
.= ( ( - p ) . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A10,FUNCT_1:13;
hence thesis by A4,CARD_1:def 7;
end;
A11: ( width ( - M1 ) ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
A12: ( len ( - p ) ) = ( len p ) by A4,CARD_1:def 7;
then A13: ( dom ( - p ) ) = ( Seg ( len p ) ) by FINSEQ_1:def 3;
(for i,j being Nat holds (([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( - M1 ) ) & i >= j) implies ( ( - M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( - r ) . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len r ) ) + 1 ) )))
proof
let i being Nat,j being Nat;
